def: A device. See Impresa.An imprese, as the Italians call it, is a device in picture with hismotto or word, borne by noble or learned personages. Camden.
A cutaneous eruption, consisting of large, round pustules, uponan indurated and inflamed base. Dunglison.
A kind of machine gun; -- named after its inventor, Hiram S.Maxim.
An escutcheon or ensign armorial; now generally applied to thefuneral shield commonly called hatchment. Cussans.
One who desires, asks, or wishes.
A projecting bonnet or shade to protect the complexion; also, awide-brimmed hat. [Obs.]
A learned man; a man acquainted with literature; -- chieflyused in the plural.Now we are to consider that our bright ideal of a literatus maychance to be maimed. De Quincey.
One who deals in wine; a wine seller, or wine merchant.
